Dialogue: 0,0:00:15.43,0:00:18.39,Lucy-Song-Title,,0,0,0,,[I want to be a rainbow]
Dialogue: 0,0:00:18.68,0:00:29.86,Lucy-Song-Japanese,,0,0,0,,Wasurenai wa hoshifuru yoru ni chikatta kotoba
Dialogue: 0,0:00:30.10,0:00:36.82,Lucy-Song-Japanese,,0,0,0,,Kono tomoshibi wo keshi wa shinai to
Dialogue: 0,0:00:37.06,0:00:47.90,Lucy-Song-Japanese,,0,0,0,,Wasurenai wa akane no asa ni chikatta kotoba
Dialogue: 0,0:00:48.16,0:00:56.88,Lucy-Song-Japanese,,0,0,0,,Wakaba ni somaru haru wo yobou to
Dialogue: 0,0:00:57.13,0:01:08.76,Lucy-Song-Japanese,,0,0,0,,Ono utsu hibiki michi hiraku utagoe
Dialogue: 0,0:01:09.01,0:01:20.66,Lucy-Song-Japanese,,0,0,0,,Kodama ga mune ni hazunde kuru no
Dialogue: 0,0:01:20.90,0:01:26.51,Lucy-Song-Japanese,,0,0,0,,Kono oosora no niji ni naritai
Dialogue: 0,0:01:26.75,0:01:36.30,Lucy-Song-Japanese,,0,0,0,,Kibou ni todoku niji ni naritai
Dialogue: 0,0:00:18.68,0:00:29.86,Lucy-Song-English,,0,0,0,,I won't forget the vow I made on that starry night
Dialogue: 0,0:00:30.10,0:00:36.82,Lucy-Song-English,,0,0,0,,To not let this flame die
Dialogue: 0,0:00:37.06,0:00:47.90,Lucy-Song-English,,0,0,0,,I won't forget the vow made on that brilliant red morning
Dialogue: 0,0:00:48.16,0:00:56.88,Lucy-Song-English,,0,0,0,,To call out for spring, dyed with young leaves
Dialogue: 0,0:00:57.13,0:01:08.76,Lucy-Song-English,,0,0,0,,Cutting axes open up roads, under the sound of singing
Dialogue: 0,0:01:09.01,0:01:20.66,Lucy-Song-English,,0,0,0,,The echoes bounce around in my chest
Dialogue: 0,0:01:20.90,0:01:26.51,Lucy-Song-English,,0,0,0,,I want to be a rainbow in this big sky
Dialogue: 0,0:01:26.75,0:01:36.30,Lucy-Song-English,,0,0,0,,I want to be a rainbow that reaches out to hope
Dialogue: 0,0:01:43.42,0:01:47.75,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,{\pos(320,306.667)\fade(100,110)}Ep. 06 - A City Called Adelaide
Dialogue: 0,0:01:50.17,0:01:52.28,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,Good! Lower it!
Dialogue: 0,0:01:58.74,0:02:00.92,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,Good! It's lowered!
Dialogue: 0,0:02:12.30,0:02:15.28,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,Ah! They're going at it with the dog!
Dialogue: 0,0:02:15.32,0:02:18.29,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,- Hey! Jerk!\N- Hey! Wait!
Dialogue: 0,0:02:19.80,0:02:21.91,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,That's Mr. Pettywell's dog.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:21.97,0:02:23.73,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,Did he steal something again?
Dialogue: 0,0:02:23.78,0:02:25.47,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,But it makes me sad when they mistreat him.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:26.11,0:02:27.83,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,I'm sorry for making you wait.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:27.85,0:02:29.46,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,Let's go now.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:29.50,0:02:30.41,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,- Okay.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:31.44,0:02:33.37,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,The weather is fine today.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:33.53,0:02:36.91,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,My father and brother\Nhave gone to Adelaide.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:37.02,0:02:41.81,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,Lucy-May and I will be\Nhelping mother clean up and do the laundry.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:52.52,0:02:54.67,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,- Wait!\N- Wait! Jerk!.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:55.54,0:02:56.56,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,Huh?
Dialogue: 0,0:02:57.21,0:03:00.14,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,Hey! You're messing\Nwith Happy again?
Dialogue: 0,0:03:00.28,0:03:03.10,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,Well, that dog is a thief, sir.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:03.19,0:03:04.35,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,What are you saying?
Dialogue: 0,0:03:04.57,0:03:07.43,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,It's true, he filched a piece of\Ndried meat from our tent.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:09.00,0:03:11.03,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,What a ridiculous accusation!
Dialogue: 0,0:03:11.06,0:03:13.30,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,Happy is decisively not a thief!
Dialogue: 0,0:03:13.48,0:03:14.84,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,Right, Happy?
Dialogue: 0,0:03:15.01,0:03:16.51,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,We know everything.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:16.57,0:03:17.72,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,Know what?
Dialogue: 0,0:03:17.92,0:03:20.58,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,That dog stole\NMr. Popple's meat last time.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:20.65,0:03:21.82,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,What did you say?
Dialogue: 0,0:03:21.84,0:03:22.73,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,- Ah!
Dialogue: 0,0:03:22.81,0:03:25.92,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,If there's no evidence,\NI won't tolerate you saying such nonsense!
Dialogue: 0,0:03:25.98,0:03:27.00,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,- Wah!
Dialogue: 0,0:03:27.03,0:03:28.60,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,That dog is a thief!
Dialogue: 0,0:03:28.64,0:03:32.46,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,And a thief dog owner \Nis by extension a thief, too!
Dialogue: 0,0:03:32.78,0:03:33.86,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,Hey!
Dialogue: 0,0:03:33.96,0:03:36.34,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,Damn brats! You'll pay for this!
Dialogue: 0,0:03:36.39,0:03:38.19,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,Darling, what has happened?
Dialogue: 0,0:03:38.21,0:03:40.03,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,You see, those brats just...
Dialogue: 0,0:03:40.20,0:03:42.32,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,I don't care for what those children did.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:42.40,0:03:45.27,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,Before anything else, you need to\Ngo to Adelaide as soon as possible
Dialogue: 0,0:03:45.40,0:03:47.25,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,and find us a proper house.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:47.32,0:03:50.21,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,Living in these conditions\Nis unbearable for me!
Dialogue: 0,0:03:50.41,0:03:52.10,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,It's unbearable for me as well.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:52.13,0:03:55.88,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,But even if I go to Adelaide, I might not\Nfind a good place there either.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:55.91,0:03:58.12,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,Adam said he wasn't able\Nto find anything.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:58.17,0:04:01.12,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,Darling, do you really trust\Na servant's word?
Dialogue: 0,0:04:01.22,0:04:03.14,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,You need to confirm it yourself.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:03.16,0:04:05.53,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,Yes, I understand, I just need to go, right?
Dialogue: 0,0:04:06.52,0:04:07.61,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,Damn it!
Dialogue: 0,0:04:10.58,0:04:11.55,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,Darling!
Dialogue: 0,0:04:11.64,0:04:14.84,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,As soon as we arrive here, \Nyou're suddenly a kleptomaniac!
Dialogue: 0,0:04:31.28,0:04:32.67,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,Tighter!
Dialogue: 0,0:04:32.70,0:04:33.88,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,Mmmm.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:33.94,0:04:35.94,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,Like this!
Dialogue: 0,0:04:37.28,0:04:39.95,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,Good! Like that!
Dialogue: 0,0:04:43.66,0:04:45.64,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,What are you two doing over there?
Dialogue: 0,0:04:45.76,0:04:48.41,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,You'll rip the clothes apart\Nif you squeeze them like that.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:52.23,0:04:55.04,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,Oh! Good morning, Mr. Parker.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:55.12,0:04:56.89,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,Yes, good morning.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:56.95,0:05:00.44,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,Your husband went to Adelaide today, correct?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:01.12,0:05:02.11,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,Yes.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:02.18,0:05:05.50,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,They left early this morning, \Nso they're probably already there.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:05.52,0:05:08.52,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,I'm sure they'll find a good place.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:08.85,0:05:09.91,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,Yes.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:09.94,0:05:12.66,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,Mr. Pettywell has also gone to Adelaide.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:12.71,0:05:14.26,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,I just saw him now.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:14.42,0:05:20.47,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,Didn't he say he wants that prefabricated home \Nyou brought over from England?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:21.25,0:05:24.62,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,My husband made it very clear \Nhe wasn't going to sell it.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:24.93,0:05:29.11,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,I'm sure, in Adelaide they already have \Nsome marvelous houses for sale.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:29.15,0:05:32.88,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,Building a house from the ground up \Nwill take some days.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:32.96,0:05:36.94,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,That's why it's not hard to see \Nwhy he'd want your prefabricated house instead.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:37.72,0:05:40.96,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,Oh! If you're here to do laundry, \Nyou can put your clothes with mine.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:41.05,0:05:43.44,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,No, it's not necessary.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:44.34,0:05:48.07,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,After all these years, \NI've gotten quite good with laundry.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:48.31,0:05:50.59,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,I've lived on my own\Nfor a very long time, you know?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:57.96,0:05:59.73,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,Why do you think it is?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:59.77,0:06:00.78,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,What is?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:00.83,0:06:04.89,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,Why I haven't been able to find\Nthat cute little bear again?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:05.23,0:06:07.61,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,Lucy-May, by chance, did you see a koala?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:07.68,0:06:09.53,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,Huh? So it's called a koala?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:09.56,0:06:12.18,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,Yes, the natives call them that.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:12.27,0:06:15.38,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,It seems to only live in Australia.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:15.60,0:06:18.78,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,But around here,\Nthere doesn't seem to be any.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:19.00,0:06:21.76,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,We saw a native boy \Nkeeping one as a pet.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:21.85,0:06:24.78,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,Oh? I guess you can see some\Nover here then.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:25.77,0:06:28.69,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,I see, so they're called Koalas, huh?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:36.35,0:06:37.44,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,Ah.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:37.48,0:06:39.86,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,Oh my, now we'll have to wash\Nthose clothes all over again.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:39.95,0:06:41.25,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,I'm sorry.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:41.55,0:06:44.11,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,Go back to the river and wash them again.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:44.33,0:06:45.57,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,It's just...
Dialogue: 0,0:06:45.59,0:06:48.76,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,What do you mean "it's just"?\NYou got it dirty when you fell down.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:49.64,0:06:50.61,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,Kate.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:50.78,0:06:52.62,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,Please go with her too.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:52.67,0:06:55.42,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,Lucy-May can't wring the clothes \Nwell enough by herself.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:55.74,0:06:56.57,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,What about this?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:56.60,0:06:59.31,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,I can take that back myself, now give it to me.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:01.96,0:07:04.41,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,In the end, you're a hopeless person,\Nyou know that?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:04.81,0:07:06.27,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,Let's go and wash it, Lucy-May.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:06.58,0:07:09.07,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,Ah! Wait! Sister!
Dialogue: 0,0:07:10.91,0:07:12.82,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,They're adorable.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:12.85,0:07:14.77,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,Those girls are hopeless.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:23.77,0:07:25.98,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,Marsh... Marsh.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:30.85,0:07:31.85,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,Marsh.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:34.99,0:07:37.88,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,Marsh! Marsh!
Dialogue: 0,0:07:38.67,0:07:40.11,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,What's wrong, Tob?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:41.90,0:07:43.12,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,Marsh.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:43.77,0:07:45.45,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,You shouldn't mess with Marsh, you know?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:48.70,0:07:50.87,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,Oh my, where did Marsh go?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:54.00,0:07:55.41,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,Welcome back!
Dialogue: 0,0:07:55.46,0:07:57.24,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,Have you set up the rope for the clothes?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:57.65,0:07:59.09,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,What happened to Kate and Lucy-May?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:02.06,0:08:06.11,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,Lucy-May! We need to hurry and\Ngo wash those clothes, right now!
Dialogue: 0,0:08:06.16,0:08:07.65,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,Just wait a moment.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:08.30,0:08:09.94,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,I'm sure I saw it.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:09.94,0:08:12.22,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,I doubt there's even a goat\Naround this place.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:12.35,0:08:13.48,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,So let's hurry up.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:13.59,0:08:16.52,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,Shhh, can't you hear?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:19.65,0:08:21.70,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,You're right, it's a goat.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:22.64,0:08:25.68,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,But why is it\Nin a place like this?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:19.30,0:09:20.31,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,Hmm?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:21.29,0:09:22.36,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,Ah!
Dialogue: 0,0:09:23.22,0:09:24.62,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,You rascal!
Dialogue: 0,0:09:28.55,0:09:30.73,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,Now I'll have to go and wash these\Nall over again.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:39.81,0:09:44.13,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,Ah! Don't do that!\NYou'll hurt its leg even more if you do!
Dialogue: 0,0:09:44.19,0:09:47.60,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,But if I don't,\Nthen we can't free it from here.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:52.48,0:09:55.12,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,Kate! Lucy-May!\NAre you the ones over there?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:55.50,0:09:56.85,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,Yes, it's us!
Dialogue: 0,0:09:56.88,0:09:58.42,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,What are you doing?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:58.48,0:10:00.09,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,Help us, Mr. Parker!
Dialogue: 0,0:10:00.30,0:10:01.25,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,Huh?
Dialogue: 0,0:10:19.83,0:10:21.31,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,Oh my, it's a goat.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:22.48,0:10:24.10,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,Why is it here?
Dialogue: 0,0:10:24.20,0:10:26.56,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,It was already like this when we found it.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:27.06,0:10:30.63,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,Hmmm, it looks like it has\Na nasty injury on its leg.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:30.88,0:10:35.11,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,Mr. Parker, please help us\Nget the goat's leg out of the tree roots.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:35.17,0:10:36.13,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,Sure.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:41.65,0:10:44.37,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,Mr. Parker! The goat is in pain!
Dialogue: 0,0:10:44.56,0:10:48.22,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,I see, but then what can we do?
Dialogue: 0,0:10:51.24,0:10:52.64,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,Hmm. Oh! I know.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:55.48,0:10:58.09,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,I always have it in my pocket.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:58.12,0:10:59.58,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,I have a knife.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:00.14,0:11:01.85,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,Ah! Thank goodness.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:02.42,0:11:04.53,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,Mr. Parker! You can't!
Dialogue: 0,0:11:04.85,0:11:06.11,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,Huh? Why not?
Dialogue: 0,0:11:06.36,0:11:08.69,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,You're going to cut off\N the goat's leg, aren't you?!
Dialogue: 0,0:11:08.74,0:11:09.72,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,Huh?
Dialogue: 0,0:11:10.01,0:11:11.01,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,Oh.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:13.04,0:11:15.70,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,No, what I'll try to cut off is the roots.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:15.78,0:11:17.61,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,It's going to be a while, but...
Dialogue: 0,0:11:18.14,0:11:20.42,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,I can cut off even a root this thick.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:21.78,0:11:23.20,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,Let's begin.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:12.80,0:12:14.02,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,Good morning.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:14.59,0:12:16.13,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,Hmm? Oh, yes.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:18.18,0:12:20.57,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,Is Adelaide far from here?
Dialogue: 0,0:12:21.18,0:12:22.90,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,This is Adelaide.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:22.93,0:12:23.87,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,Huh?
Dialogue: 0,0:12:26.51,0:12:28.48,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,There's not a single house in sight.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:28.65,0:12:30.20,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,This is Adelaide.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:30.48,0:12:34.93,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,This is a park area that surrounds the town, \Nnow and in the future.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:35.07,0:12:38.18,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,It was Colonel Light who drew up \Nthe layout for the town.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:38.56,0:12:40.37,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,A park surrounding the town?
Dialogue: 0,0:12:40.44,0:12:41.43,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,That's right.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:42.35,0:12:45.61,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,But for now, the town itself \Nalso looks more like a park.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:45.92,0:12:48.90,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,There aren't many constructed houses\Nand there aren't many people.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:50.07,0:12:52.43,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,Isn't the population over 300 already?
Dialogue: 0,0:12:52.48,0:12:53.71,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,That's right.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:53.92,0:12:56.40,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,Still, so far, only the roads were built.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:56.43,0:13:00.47,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,Only straight roads that run from east to west, \Nfrom north to south.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:00.58,0:13:02.23,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,So only the streets have been built?
Dialogue: 0,0:13:02.41,0:13:05.46,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,Speaking of which, \Nwhere are you guys heading for?
Dialogue: 0,0:13:13.94,0:13:16.09,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,This must be Colonel Light's office, right?
Dialogue: 0,0:13:16.34,0:13:17.37,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,That's right.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:18.29,0:13:21.10,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,Dad, should we finish our business here first?
Dialogue: 0,0:13:21.29,0:13:24.16,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,Or maybe we'll try to procure the cart first?
Dialogue: 0,0:13:29.64,0:13:32.21,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,We're going to be here for a long while.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:33.88,0:13:36.09,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,Then we should go and find a cart first, right?
Dialogue: 0,0:13:36.11,0:13:37.13,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,You're right, Ben.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:37.16,0:13:40.49,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,But not just any cart. It's an oxcart \Nthat Mr. Jamling's managed to secure for us.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:43.14,0:13:45.39,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,It's because an ox \Nis stronger than a horse, right?
Dialogue: 0,0:13:46.47,0:13:49.08,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,Yes, even if we get a cart
Dialogue: 0,0:13:49.16,0:13:51.61,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,what's the use of it when there's still \Nso few horses around?
Dialogue: 0,0:13:52.09,0:13:56.01,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,Father, if Mr. Jamling had already \Nmade a contract for an oxcart,
Dialogue: 0,0:13:56.05,0:13:57.69,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,doesn't it mean we can tend to that later?
Dialogue: 0,0:13:58.25,0:13:59.88,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,Let's settle on our plot first.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:00.29,0:14:02.56,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,You're correct in what you say.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:17.27,0:14:18.97,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,With this, it should be fine.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:19.00,0:14:21.00,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,Thank you very much, Mr. Parker.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:21.04,0:14:23.37,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,Are you sure you didn't need \Nthat shirt, Mr. Parker?
Dialogue: 0,0:14:23.49,0:14:25.60,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,Yes, this was just an old shirt, you know.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:25.66,0:14:28.35,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,Anyway, are you thinking of taking the goat home?
Dialogue: 0,0:14:28.38,0:14:31.45,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,Since I found it, then that means\NI can keep it, right?
Dialogue: 0,0:14:31.79,0:14:34.66,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,Yes, but only if the owner\Ndoesn't show up, you know?
Dialogue: 0,0:14:34.74,0:14:36.50,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,I'm sure that it got lost.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:36.54,0:14:38.79,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,Then its owner \Nmust be looking for it, right?
Dialogue: 0,0:14:38.82,0:14:39.88,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,Most probably.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:39.92,0:14:43.37,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,If the owner appears I'll return it,\Nbut until then I'll look after it.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:44.34,0:14:45.52,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,Hmm?
Dialogue: 0,0:14:48.08,0:14:49.21,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,Oh my.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:49.47,0:14:51.32,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,What's wrong, Mr. Parker?
Dialogue: 0,0:14:52.45,0:14:53.63,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,Hmm.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:55.85,0:15:00.44,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,Oh-ho, what do you know! \NThis goat got a baby goat in her belly!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:00.59,0:15:02.10,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,Huh? Really?
Dialogue: 0,0:15:02.28,0:15:04.66,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,When will it be born, Mr. Parker?
Dialogue: 0,0:15:04.74,0:15:07.25,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,Well, you see... I'm not sure...
Dialogue: 0,0:15:07.28,0:15:11.00,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,This is wonderful. Now\Nhurry up and be born, okay?
Dialogue: 0,0:15:11.06,0:15:12.28,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,Lucy-May.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:12.41,0:15:15.67,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,This goat isn't yours yet, you know?
Dialogue: 0,0:15:15.72,0:15:18.11,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,Can you walk? Tell me, can you walk?
Dialogue: 0,0:15:18.16,0:15:22.96,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,Are you okay? Now, let's try walking slowly. \NLike that, slowly, slowly.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:22.99,0:15:25.28,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,Let's go home now.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:37.99,0:15:42.10,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,How will Adelaide look like in the future? \NHere is our rough idea of it.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:43.42,0:15:46.77,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,Surely, you don't intend to build \Nthe same city as on this blueprint?
Dialogue: 0,0:15:47.09,0:15:51.59,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,No, the Colonel's order was \Nto follow this blueprint exactly.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:52.30,0:15:55.21,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,Presently, we're building the roads \Naccording to this blueprint.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:55.32,0:15:56.63,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,I see.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:57.06,0:15:59.74,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,By the way, I was planning to run a farm here.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:59.79,0:16:01.98,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,That's what we came to Southern Australia for.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:02.47,0:16:05.29,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,Is there any similar map for the farmlands?
Dialogue: 0,0:16:05.69,0:16:09.90,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,Actually, we haven't made much progress at all\Nin surveying the farmland.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:10.46,0:16:11.53,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,What does that mean?
Dialogue: 0,0:16:11.97,0:16:13.38,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,What I'm trying to say... well...
Dialogue: 0,0:16:13.44,0:16:18.70,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,It will take a little longer for the farmland \Nto come into your possession.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:19.47,0:16:20.99,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,How long will it take?
Dialogue: 0,0:16:21.14,0:16:22.78,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,Well you see... I can't say...
Dialogue: 0,0:16:22.89,0:16:27.49,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,After all, the surveying is lagging behind, \Nwhile the applicants are numerous.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:28.08,0:16:30.07,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,Then, for how long do I have to wait?
Dialogue: 0,0:16:30.20,0:16:32.24,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,One year or maybe two years.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:32.27,0:16:33.53,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,What did you say?
Dialogue: 0,0:16:33.60,0:16:36.92,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,Well, in either case, I can't say with exact certainty...
Dialogue: 0,0:16:36.94,0:16:39.03,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,Then, who can tell me for certain?
Dialogue: 0,0:16:39.06,0:16:41.39,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,Well... I don't think anyone knows for sure.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:41.57,0:16:44.19,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,Not even the Surveyor General Colonel Light?
Dialogue: 0,0:16:44.31,0:16:48.06,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,The Colonel is currently away \Non a surveying mission in the northern parts.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:48.18,0:16:50.52,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,But even if you could ask Colonel directly...
Dialogue: 0,0:16:50.63,0:16:54.01,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,it's probable that he might\Nnot be able to give you an answer.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:54.06,0:16:56.16,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,That's not even close \Nto what we've been promised!
Dialogue: 0,0:16:56.47,0:16:59.47,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,The reason I came all the way here \Nto Southern Australia...
Dialogue: 0,0:16:59.62,0:17:03.28,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,was to build a splendid farm, \Nbecause you have plenty of land for it.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:03.35,0:17:06.37,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,We were told that as soon as we get here, \Nyou'll give us the land right away.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:06.68,0:17:11.10,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,But sir, you have to understand: you can't just randomly subdivide land that hasn't been surveyed yet.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:11.21,0:17:13.71,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,For now, there is just no other way \Nbut to wait and see.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:13.98,0:17:16.51,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,But then, what in the world \Ndo you want me to do?
Dialogue: 0,0:17:16.78,0:17:18.78,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,I've been a farmer for my whole life.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:18.99,0:17:21.11,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,So I can't even imagine myself doing any other job.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:21.28,0:17:24.58,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,Right now, they're constructing \Nthe streets in the city.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:24.69,0:17:27.91,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,In the mountains to the east, \Nthe logging is in the full swing.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:28.15,0:17:31.49,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,The craftsmen who build houses \Nare also in a very short supply.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:31.59,0:17:33.98,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,What I mean is, we've got \Nplenty of jobs available.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:36.04,0:17:39.23,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,It isn't just you, many are in the same situation.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:43.15,0:17:46.52,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,In that case... I just want a piece of land in the city.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:46.96,0:17:48.91,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,Are you planning to build a house?
Dialogue: 0,0:17:49.54,0:17:54.18,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,From England, we brought along \Na prefabricated home, although it's still on the ship.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:54.23,0:17:56.33,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,How are you planning to bring it \Nall the way here?
Dialogue: 0,0:17:56.51,0:17:57.77,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,By oxcart.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:57.98,0:18:01.65,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,You'll have to divide it into several runs. \NThat might take up to a month of time.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:01.85,0:18:03.60,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,Until then, are you planning\Nto live in a tent?
Dialogue: 0,0:18:04.86,0:18:08.30,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,No, I never even thought \Nthings might come to this.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:09.36,0:18:12.39,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,How about I offer you \Nto buy not only land, but a house, too?
Dialogue: 0,0:18:15.26,0:18:17.59,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,Actually, there is one that comes to mind...
Dialogue: 0,0:18:18.28,0:18:19.59,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,Just land would be enough.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:19.82,0:18:23.03,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,Well, if it's just the land you need, \Nyou're free to settle wherever you please.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:23.25,0:18:25.76,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,But we don't have much plots with houses.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:25.87,0:18:28.84,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,Our housing can't really keep up \Nwith the rapid population growth.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:29.09,0:18:31.12,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,For me... the land is enough.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:40.78,0:18:42.58,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,It's a rather small house, isn't it?
Dialogue: 0,0:18:42.92,0:18:45.15,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,You can't really call this a house.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:45.97,0:18:48.18,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,We can still build \Nour prefabricated home here, right?
Dialogue: 0,0:18:48.52,0:18:50.08,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,Hmm? Yeah.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:50.22,0:18:52.22,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,We could use that house for storage,\Ncouldn't we?
Dialogue: 0,0:18:59.36,0:19:01.57,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,Am I finally seeing my new neighbors?
Dialogue: 0,0:19:01.76,0:19:03.78,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,Oh, no, we haven't decided yet.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:04.22,0:19:06.37,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,I'm Jane Mac, nice to meet you.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:06.67,0:19:07.39,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,Yes.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:07.94,0:19:10.50,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,You've heard about this house \Nfrom my brother, right?
Dialogue: 0,0:19:10.58,0:19:11.46,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,Huh?
Dialogue: 0,0:19:11.55,0:19:14.28,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,My brother works \Nin Colonel Light's office
Dialogue: 0,0:19:14.45,0:19:16.78,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,and my husband right now \Nis working alongside Colonel.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:16.83,0:19:19.01,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,Ah! That means \Nthe man we met earlier was...
Dialogue: 0,0:19:19.96,0:19:22.15,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,I'm certain it was\Nmy brother, Bernard.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:22.85,0:19:26.11,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,I'm Arthur Popple,\Nand this is my son Ben.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:26.66,0:19:30.02,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,I only came to see the house \Nbecause I was curious.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:30.17,0:19:31.53,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,I always tell my brother,
Dialogue: 0,0:19:31.65,0:19:35.84,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,"If you're inviting someone to become our neighbor, \Nmake sure they're a good person first."
Dialogue: 0,0:19:36.38,0:19:39.51,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,Yes, well, we're going to look\Ninside the house.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:46.94,0:19:48.20,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,It can't be.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:48.25,0:19:50.85,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,Then, what happened \Nto your contract with Mr. Jamling?
Dialogue: 0,0:19:51.29,0:19:54.83,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,Mr. Jamling injured his leg \Nand can't move for now, correct?
Dialogue: 0,0:19:55.17,0:19:56.51,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,How did you know that?
Dialogue: 0,0:19:56.96,0:19:58.57,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,Someone told me.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:58.66,0:20:03.18,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,That's why I canceled my contract with Mr. Jamling \Nand that oxcart now goes to Mr. Pettywell.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:03.28,0:20:04.65,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,Did you say Mr. Pettywell?
Dialogue: 0,0:20:04.67,0:20:05.95,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,Oh! I said it.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:06.58,0:20:08.59,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,Well, you would've found out sooner or later.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:08.95,0:20:09.95,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,That's right.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:10.01,0:20:12.18,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,That marvelously strong ox
Dialogue: 0,0:20:12.24,0:20:15.69,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,is to start working for Mr. Pettywell \Nthe day after tomorrow.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:16.17,0:20:18.27,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,But I'm very sorry for you.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:18.76,0:20:20.56,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,Is there no one else with an ox in the area?
Dialogue: 0,0:20:20.59,0:20:21.45,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,Well...
Dialogue: 0,0:20:21.48,0:20:24.48,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,Pretty sure everyone had already \Nsigned a contract for an ox.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:24.53,0:20:26.45,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,Shouldn't be a lot of them, if any.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:26.79,0:20:28.75,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,Then are you saying I won't find anyone?
Dialogue: 0,0:20:28.88,0:20:30.10,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,I guess so...
Dialogue: 0,0:20:30.24,0:20:34.19,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,But I was so relieved to hear Mr. Jamling \Nhad already secured a contract.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:34.44,0:20:37.39,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,Again with the same story as before?
Dialogue: 0,0:20:37.44,0:20:39.89,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,I've made a new contract\Nwith Mr. Pettywell.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:39.96,0:20:41.50,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,Moreover, he paid in advance!
Dialogue: 0,0:20:42.00,0:20:43.36,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,What did you say?
Dialogue: 0,0:20:46.38,0:20:48.54,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,Negotiations went sour?
Dialogue: 0,0:20:49.05,0:20:52.10,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,No, the negotiations \Nare already concluded, Mr. Pettywell.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:52.18,0:20:53.87,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,Oh, I'm glad then.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:53.90,0:20:56.54,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,Come on, boy, come here \Nand drink some more with me.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:56.66,0:20:58.41,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,Thanks for the offer!
Dialogue: 0,0:20:59.15,0:21:00.75,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,You heard what I said.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:03.31,0:21:05.41,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,That Mr. Pettywell is the worst.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:06.71,0:21:08.48,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,Whatever the case, let's try somewhere else.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:08.76,0:21:12.97,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,The day after tomorrow, be it an ox or a horse, \Nwe need some animal to move our things.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:15.47,0:21:16.72,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,Hey, you!
Dialogue: 0,0:21:17.00,0:21:20.21,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,I just remembered I've got \None wheelbarrow to spare. How about that?
Dialogue: 0,0:21:23.48,0:21:27.16,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,Tsk, try to be friendly\Nand this is how you're treated.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:15.96,0:22:17.29,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,I've put Tob to bed.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:17.38,0:22:18.66,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,Thank you.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:19.07,0:22:21.78,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,What do you think happened\Nto father and Ben?
Dialogue: 0,0:22:21.90,0:22:23.91,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,They're simply a bit late, nothing more.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:24.59,0:22:28.16,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,Do you think they'll manage \Nto get through that forest when it's so dark?
Dialogue: 0,0:22:30.37,0:22:33.13,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,What should I name you?
Dialogue: 0,0:22:33.20,0:22:37.55,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,Nobody has come to look for you,\Nso I suppose that means you're mine.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:37.78,0:22:39.23,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,Lucy-May.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:39.65,0:22:40.79,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,What is it?
Dialogue: 0,0:22:41.35,0:22:43.23,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,You're so carefree, you know that?
Dialogue: 0,0:22:43.56,0:22:46.53,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,We're all so worried about dad!
Dialogue: 0,0:22:46.59,0:22:48.57,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,But you're only thinking about that goat.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:48.66,0:22:50.90,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,I'm also worried!
Dialogue: 0,0:22:50.58,0:22:51.27,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,- No you're not.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:51.57,0:22:55.36,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,I'm talking to her because I worry about dad \Nand try to get my mind off it!
Dialogue: 0,0:22:55.43,0:22:56.20,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,Liar!
Dialogue: 0,0:22:56.67,0:22:58.29,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,You're an idiot, sister!
Dialogue: 0,0:22:58.37,0:22:59.72,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,Why are you calling me an idiot?
Dialogue: 0,0:22:59.75,0:23:01.76,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,I'm calling you an idiot\Nbecause you are an idiot!
Dialogue: 0,0:23:01.78,0:23:02.83,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,What did you say?
Dialogue: 0,0:23:03.08,0:23:04.71,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,That's enough, you two!
Dialogue: 0,0:23:04.98,0:23:06.09,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,Mmm!
Dialogue: 0,0:23:20.89,0:23:23.06,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,That ship that brought us here -
Dialogue: 0,0:23:23.15,0:23:25.23,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,the day after tomorrow, \Nit departs for England.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:25.25,0:23:28.05,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,The day after tomorrow? \NThey're running ahead of schedule.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:28.41,0:23:30.08,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,That's what John told me.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:30.21,0:23:33.58,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,Tomorrow, we definitely need \Nto unload the rest of our luggage.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:33.70,0:23:34.88,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,You're right.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:36.74,0:23:38.56,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,What happened to your father?
Dialogue: 0,0:23:38.65,0:23:39.62,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,I wonder, too.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:40.90,0:23:45.33,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,It became completely dark, \Nbut dad and brother hadn't returned yet.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:45.89,0:23:49.78,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,We were just sitting there silently \Nfor what seemed to be an eternity.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:55.62,0:23:58.14,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,I wonder what happened to dad.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:03.78,0:24:06.98,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,Dad and brother never returned \Neven when it's gotten very late.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:07.06,0:24:10.16,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,Could they have taken the wrong road and got lost?
Dialogue: 0,0:24:10.36,0:24:13.77,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,Next on Lucy-May of the Southern Rainbow:\N"Ben's Bad Luck".
Dialogue: 0,0:24:13.79,0:24:14.98,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,Don't miss it!
